  "articleSummary": "The article argues that \"Generative UI\" encompasses five distinct but often conflated approaches, each operating at different layers of the tech stack and carrying unique risks and implementation costs. It distinguishes GenUI from design-time code generation, AI-assisted form fill, and unsafe raw HTML injection, emphasizing that true runtime GenUI involves models dynamically selecting and composing pre-approved UI components based on task state. The core thesis is a framework for categorizing these approaches into three patterns—tool-to-component rendering (safest), component catalog composition (balanced), and open-ended generation (riskiest)—",
